2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed model uses artificial intelligence techniques to predict student's academic performance. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for interpreting the predictions made by the proposed model. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the potential impact of the proposed model on educational technologies and student success. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper uses graph structures to model the complex relationships between multiple courses and how students acquire knowledge across them.
